A Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court in Ikorodu, Lagos on Thursday ordered that three teenagers, who allegedly defiled a 12-year-old girl, be remanded in correctional custody, pending legal advice. The defendants are Segun Gbadebo, 18, Taiye Ishola, 17, and Samuel Adebayo, 17. Chief Magistrate A. F. Azeez did not take the pleas of the teenagers, but ordered the police to return the case file to the Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP), for legal advice. She adjourned the case until April 2.